# DIRECTUS INTEGRATION

Directus must be accessed through a dedicated integration module.

Location:

```
src/modules/directus
```

Responsibilities:

- Authenticate users via Directus
- Fetch authorization_matrix
- Fetch policy_rules
- Fetch roles if required

Directus API must be called using **axios**.

Directus base URL:

```
http://directus:8055
```

Directus must never be exposed publicly.

Only NestJS can access Directus.

---

# JWT VERIFICATION

NestJS must verify Directus JWT tokens.

Verification rules:

- Signature must match Directus SECRET
- Token must not be expired
- Issuer must match configured issuer

Example guard behavior:

```
jwt.verify(token, process.env.DIRECTUS_JWT_SECRET)

if(decoded.iss !== process.env.JWT_ISSUER)
  throw UnauthorizedException
```

Decoded user must be attached to request:

```
req.user = {
id: decoded.id,
role: decoded.role
}
```

